1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:22,000
( Watch on www.kissasia.co, .club, .be, .org, .net, .id, .xyz )

2
00:00:55,924 --> 00:00:57,092
Wow, amazing!

3
00:00:57,092 --> 00:00:58,134
The photo is nice, huh?

4
00:00:58,134 --> 00:01:01,179
What I really want is

5
00:01:01,179 --> 00:01:03,197
a perfectly ordinary day.

6
00:01:05,976 --> 00:01:08,603
What I truly wish for

7
00:01:08,603 --> 00:01:10,063
is something that's just mine.

8
00:01:10,063 --> 00:01:12,566
Through these innovations, repeat purchases...

9
00:01:12,566 --> 00:01:14,526
A full-time employee ID,

10
00:01:14,526 --> 00:01:17,019
and a decent amount of annual leave.

11
00:01:17,019 --> 00:01:19,090
A couch I picked myself,

12
00:01:19,090 --> 00:01:21,197
and a home I paid for on my own.

13
00:01:24,202 --> 00:01:26,604
Who would've ever imagined...

14
00:01:27,247 --> 00:01:28,815
One random day,

15
00:01:29,791 --> 00:01:31,835
someone would barge into

16
00:01:31,835 --> 00:01:33,538
my peaceful routine...

17
00:01:33,538 --> 00:01:36,188
and completely wreck my space,

18
00:01:37,197 --> 00:01:39,724
just by showing up.

19
00:01:43,054 --> 00:01:45,291
[Here Woo Joo comes]

20
00:01:47,225 --> 00:01:50,145
Like a disaster.

21
00:01:50,145 --> 00:01:51,705
Like a bomb.

22
00:01:53,690 --> 00:01:55,770
Dropping out of the sky.

23
00:01:59,786 --> 00:02:03,256
In my universe, I was everything.

24
00:02:03,256 --> 00:02:05,115
Then another "universe"

25
00:02:16,171 --> 00:02:18,990
- suddenly dropped into it.
- suddenly dropped into it.

26
00:02:26,043 --> 00:02:28,636
[Episode 1]

27
00:02:54,334 --> 00:02:55,919
The natural light looks good.

28
00:02:55,919 --> 00:02:57,337
Can we lose the reflector?

29
00:02:57,337 --> 00:02:59,403
The bounce is throwing off the tone.

30
00:03:04,752 --> 00:03:05,832
Hey, hey.

31
00:03:05,832 --> 00:03:06,972
Your head's in the frame.

32
00:03:06,972 --> 00:03:09,277
Higher, higher!

33
00:03:09,277 --> 00:03:10,377
I'm gonna fall in the water.

34
00:03:10,377 --> 00:03:12,105
Go back further!

35
00:03:15,563 --> 00:03:17,023
Hey, come in closer. Closer.

36
00:03:17,023 --> 00:03:18,082
Step in more.

37
00:03:18,082 --> 00:03:19,430
Drop the angle.

38
00:03:19,430 --> 00:03:20,903
The angle? Got it.

39
00:03:27,367 --> 00:03:28,851
Sorry.

40
00:03:42,590 --> 00:03:43,633
[22,779 steps]

41
00:03:54,568 --> 00:03:56,687
[Delivery completed]

42
00:03:56,687 --> 00:03:57,712
[38,088 steps achieved]

43
00:03:57,712 --> 00:03:59,727
[30,125 steps]

44
00:04:02,527 --> 00:04:04,053
It's raining.

45
00:04:05,280 --> 00:04:08,933
Yay! Change of plans!

46
00:04:10,535 --> 00:04:12,645
When was the last time we got this lucky?

47
00:04:12,645 --> 00:04:14,270
[Rainy Day Sale]
Rainy days are best

48
00:04:14,270 --> 00:04:15,832
for the fresh section, right?

49
00:04:15,832 --> 00:04:18,192
The bundle deals are a steal.

50
00:04:18,781 --> 00:04:21,683
Looks like breakfast is covered for a while.

51
00:04:22,397 --> 00:04:24,399
They always discount raw food when it rains.

52
00:04:24,399 --> 00:04:25,206
[Time Sale 30%]

53
00:04:25,206 --> 00:04:26,681
Wait.

54
00:04:27,719 --> 00:04:29,137
Oh, hey!

55
00:04:29,137 --> 00:04:32,039
In ten seconds...

56
00:04:32,724 --> 00:04:34,350
Look.

57
00:04:34,350 --> 00:04:36,644
[Seafood Section]
We're starting the closing sale now.

58
00:04:36,644 --> 00:04:38,796
[Time Sale 30%]
The closing sale begins now.

59
00:04:38,796 --> 00:04:39,731
[Closing Sale]

60
00:04:39,731 --> 00:04:41,900
We're starting the closing sale now.

61
00:04:41,900 --> 00:04:43,445
The closing sale begins now.

62
00:04:43,445 --> 00:04:44,986
Wow, amazing.

63
00:04:44,986 --> 00:04:47,363
Woo Hyun Joo is the best.

64
00:04:47,363 --> 00:04:49,908
This is what you call "big-sister experience."

65
00:04:49,908 --> 00:04:51,517
Right? Let's go.

66
00:04:54,913 --> 00:04:56,392
Ta-da.

67
00:04:59,495 --> 00:05:00,877
It's really coming down.

68
00:05:00,877 --> 00:05:02,499
Let's get inside.

69
00:05:03,546 --> 00:05:04,714
Hurry, hurry.

70
00:05:04,714 --> 00:05:06,758
A grocery sale and kimchi pancakes...

71
00:05:06,758 --> 00:05:09,047
I've been waiting forever
for a rainy day like this.

72
00:05:09,047 --> 00:05:12,889
So, here we go. Special Set A.

73
00:05:12,889 --> 00:05:14,387
Cheers!

74
00:05:18,186 --> 00:05:20,766
It didn't rain for ages. I was so bummed.

75
00:05:24,943 --> 00:05:27,237
I can't get this flavor if I eat out.

76
00:05:27,237 --> 00:05:30,299
Your corn recipe really is the best.

77
00:05:30,299 --> 00:05:32,742
You picked up more shifts again, right?

78
00:05:32,742 --> 00:05:33,743
Nope.

79
00:05:33,743 --> 00:05:36,538
Corn prices have gone way up lately.

80
00:05:36,538 --> 00:05:39,051
And the BS thing? Rejected?

81
00:05:40,883 --> 00:05:43,118
How did you know?

82
00:05:43,984 --> 00:05:46,965
You always overdo it when that happens.

83
00:05:46,965 --> 00:05:48,675
You get weirdly cheerful,

84
00:05:48,675 --> 00:05:50,343
and you stop answering my calls.

85
00:05:50,343 --> 00:05:51,578
I know you too well.

86
00:05:51,578 --> 00:05:53,763
It's not because of a part-time job.

87
00:05:53,763 --> 00:05:56,599
The competition's just brutal this time.

88
00:05:56,599 --> 00:05:59,428
Still, I'll land a job before I graduate.

89
00:05:59,428 --> 00:06:01,062
Hyun Jin.

90
00:06:01,062 --> 00:06:02,981
Why are you in such a rush?

91
00:06:02,981 --> 00:06:04,566
You're still young.

92
00:06:04,566 --> 00:06:06,234
And besides...

93
00:06:06,234 --> 00:06:08,427
you've got this very reliable umbrella.

94
00:06:13,908 --> 00:06:15,160
Young, my foot.

95
00:06:15,160 --> 00:06:16,369
Hey.

96
00:06:16,369 --> 00:06:19,102
I'm Woo Hyun Jin,
top of my class at Seorin University.

97
00:06:20,165 --> 00:06:21,332
By the way...

98
00:06:21,332 --> 00:06:23,992
There's something more important right now.

99
00:06:24,627 --> 00:06:25,898
- Spicy mayo?
- Correct!

100
00:06:25,898 --> 00:06:27,213
How did you know?

101
00:06:27,213 --> 00:06:28,785
Yay!

102
00:06:29,685 --> 00:06:30,998
I'll bring you your phone.

103
00:06:30,998 --> 00:06:32,785
Oh, thanks.

104
00:06:44,981 --> 00:06:46,588
Who is it?

105
00:06:47,483 --> 00:06:50,014
It's Mr. Woo Jin.

106
00:07:19,432 --> 00:07:21,718
Excuse me, Mr. Sun Woo Jin.

107
00:07:22,769 --> 00:07:24,687
So now my sister gets proposed to,

108
00:07:24,687 --> 00:07:26,911
and I don't even get a heads-up?

109
00:07:26,911 --> 00:07:28,444
This is because of me again, right?

110
00:07:28,444 --> 00:07:30,593
First it was "until I graduate,"

111
00:07:30,593 --> 00:07:32,725
and now it's "until I get a job?"

112
00:07:33,404 --> 00:07:36,349
I mean... you two are really close.

113
00:07:37,533 --> 00:07:39,304
So yeah, I get it.

114
00:07:42,372 --> 00:07:44,457
I'll give you my approval.

115
00:07:44,457 --> 00:07:47,085
I'm basically my sister's mom and dad.

116
00:07:47,085 --> 00:07:48,419
So...

117
00:07:48,419 --> 00:07:50,351
let's set up the family meeting.

118
00:07:50,351 --> 00:07:52,501
- What?
- Invite them.

119
00:07:52,501 --> 00:07:53,925
Your whole family.

120
00:07:53,925 --> 00:07:55,554
Cheers!

121
00:07:59,013 --> 00:08:01,224
That guy, Sun Tae Hyung.

122
00:08:01,224 --> 00:08:03,710
He was the one handling
the reflector assist, right?

123
00:08:03,710 --> 00:08:06,229
Before anyone even touched it,
he already had the angle locked in.

124
00:08:06,229 --> 00:08:08,356
Yeah, I thought the A-cuts
looked oddly high-end.

125
00:08:08,356 --> 00:08:09,399
You saw it, huh?

126
00:08:09,399 --> 00:08:11,166
He pulled up the references instantly.

127
00:08:11,166 --> 00:08:12,724
Thanks to him,

128
00:08:12,724 --> 00:08:16,072
the photos turned out way better,
just by a hair.

129
00:08:16,072 --> 00:08:17,918
He had to do something.

130
00:08:17,918 --> 00:08:19,951
He's street-trained.

131
00:08:19,951 --> 00:08:21,369
Not even a photography major.

132
00:08:21,369 --> 00:08:22,870
Didn't go to college either.

133
00:08:22,870 --> 00:08:25,123
Well, he had a prize
at some random local photo show.

134
00:08:25,123 --> 00:08:26,207
Other than that,

135
00:08:26,207 --> 00:08:28,481
his resume was basically blank.

136
00:08:29,741 --> 00:08:32,291
Wow, you remember all that?

137
00:08:32,291 --> 00:08:34,090
Guess you're pretty fond of me.

138
00:08:34,090 --> 00:08:35,136
Of course I am.

139
00:08:35,136 --> 00:08:37,057
A high-school grad from an orphanage

140
00:08:37,057 --> 00:08:39,888
isn't exactly common in this industry.

141
00:08:39,888 --> 00:08:41,039
True.

142
00:08:41,039 --> 00:08:44,708
But you've been leaning on
that "street-trained guy" a lot.

143
00:08:44,708 --> 00:08:46,401
Today included.

144
00:08:47,520 --> 00:08:48,730
Hey.

145
00:08:48,730 --> 00:08:50,982
Just because you're under fancy lights now,

146
00:08:50,982 --> 00:08:52,900
you think you're on the same level as me?

147
00:08:52,900 --> 00:08:53,943
Hey.

148
00:08:53,943 --> 00:08:55,449
Wake up.

149
00:08:56,044 --> 00:08:57,510
Number one, and two.

150
00:08:57,510 --> 00:09:01,075
You two are just marinated crab.

151
00:09:01,075 --> 00:09:03,495
Sucked dry and tossed aside.

152
00:09:04,814 --> 00:09:07,748
That guy doesn't even have
any sauce left to suck.

153
00:09:36,235 --> 00:09:37,945
Bro! I love you!

154
00:09:37,945 --> 00:09:39,173
What?

155
00:09:39,173 --> 00:09:40,490
You don't remember last night?

156
00:09:40,490 --> 00:09:41,574
As of yesterday,

157
00:09:41,574 --> 00:09:42,782
you're totally my role model.

158
00:09:42,782 --> 00:09:45,402
- Please be my mentor.
- What the hell are you saying?

159
00:09:46,621 --> 00:09:48,539
Hey!

160
00:09:48,539 --> 00:09:50,052
Before you start judging
where people come from,

161
00:09:50,052 --> 00:09:52,168
learn how to set your presets
and exposure first.

162
00:09:52,168 --> 00:09:53,795
Isn't it embarrassing
knowing less than an assistant?

163
00:09:53,795 --> 00:09:55,296
Okay. I quit.

164
00:09:55,296 --> 00:09:56,464
You don't even have
any sauce left to suck...

165
00:09:56,464 --> 00:09:58,132
not even a single egg.

166
00:09:58,132 --> 00:09:59,258
Check, please!

167
00:09:59,258 --> 00:10:01,031
Put it all on my card!

168
00:10:03,513 --> 00:10:04,559
Remember now?

169
00:10:04,559 --> 00:10:05,973
You were awesome last night.

170
00:10:05,973 --> 00:10:07,012
Hang up.

171
00:10:07,012 --> 00:10:08,925
Bro, wait a second...

172
00:10:16,934 --> 00:10:18,601
[Amount Paid]

173
00:10:19,858 --> 00:10:21,847
I completely lost it.

174
00:10:24,826 --> 00:10:25,935
Let's be clear.

175
00:10:25,935 --> 00:10:28,545
You didn't quit. I fired you.

176
00:10:28,545 --> 00:10:31,165
[Rent / Transportation / Credit Card Payment]
[Balance: -300,000 won]

177
00:10:31,165 --> 00:10:33,108
No...

178
00:10:33,709 --> 00:10:35,467
No!

179
00:10:47,223 --> 00:10:49,542
Yeah... it's beautiful.

180
00:11:00,570 --> 00:11:01,623
Are you not tired?

181
00:11:01,623 --> 00:11:03,514
I'm good.

182
00:11:04,722 --> 00:11:06,409
Sir, right this way please.

183
00:11:06,409 --> 00:11:07,982
Okay.

184
00:11:13,958 --> 00:11:16,031
Wow, it looks amazing.

185
00:11:34,812 --> 00:11:35,910
Let's see.

186
00:11:35,910 --> 00:11:37,690
[Balance: 1,207,000 won]

187
00:11:37,690 --> 00:11:40,050
One million two hundred and...

188
00:11:46,270 --> 00:11:47,325
What's with you?

189
00:11:47,325 --> 00:11:49,625
Why the long face?

190
00:11:50,453 --> 00:11:52,050
Se Yeon.

191
00:11:53,039 --> 00:11:54,749
Do you know this?

192
00:11:54,749 --> 00:11:56,358
- Huh?
- This.

193
00:11:57,335 --> 00:11:59,275
Oh, this is a Rorman light.

194
00:12:00,304 --> 00:12:01,904
Oh,

195
00:12:01,904 --> 00:12:03,883
You knew it.

196
00:12:03,883 --> 00:12:06,552
I used to collect lighting, remember?

197
00:12:06,552 --> 00:12:08,012
Yeah, but why this one?

198
00:12:08,012 --> 00:12:09,830
My sister says it's pretty.

199
00:12:10,515 --> 00:12:11,891
That's a first.

200
00:12:11,891 --> 00:12:14,397
She's never actually said
something was pretty before.

201
00:12:15,061 --> 00:12:17,104
Come to think of it,

202
00:12:17,104 --> 00:12:19,677
we always bought things
because we were short on something,

203
00:12:19,677 --> 00:12:20,890
or...

204
00:12:20,890 --> 00:12:23,368
because we needed them.

205
00:12:23,368 --> 00:12:25,530
So...

206
00:12:25,530 --> 00:12:28,324
this is the first thing
that's really her taste.

207
00:12:28,324 --> 00:12:30,993
That's why I really want to get it for her.

208
00:12:30,993 --> 00:12:32,913
It's just... money's kind of tight.

209
00:12:33,663 --> 00:12:34,872
Oh, right.

210
00:12:34,872 --> 00:12:36,786
Do you happen to have a Pimang ID?

211
00:12:39,001 --> 00:12:41,001
Not exactly happy to see you...

212
00:12:44,340 --> 00:12:45,741
Okay, done.

213
00:12:48,728 --> 00:12:49,845
So heavy.

214
00:12:49,845 --> 00:12:51,550
You live alone, right?

215
00:12:51,550 --> 00:12:52,848
Why is your place so nicely decorated?

216
00:12:52,848 --> 00:12:54,439
Because my space matters to me.

217
00:12:54,439 --> 00:12:55,688
You know, I'm "street-trained."

218
00:12:55,688 --> 00:12:57,937
If you wanna protect your precious space,

219
00:12:57,937 --> 00:12:59,914
start with this.

220
00:12:59,914 --> 00:13:02,191
Didn't I tell you to stop snapping
whenever your feelings get bad?

221
00:13:02,191 --> 00:13:04,392
I couldn't help it.

222
00:13:05,778 --> 00:13:07,071
Boss.

223
00:13:07,071 --> 00:13:08,489
Any chance you could spot me
an interest-free loan?

224
00:13:08,489 --> 00:13:10,032
My studio's been in the red for four months,

225
00:13:10,032 --> 00:13:11,382
and I even gave up my place.

226
00:13:11,382 --> 00:13:12,482
What are you worried about?

227
00:13:12,482 --> 00:13:14,870
Sell just one thing here and you'll be fine.

228
00:13:14,870 --> 00:13:16,914
I'll make sure it sells.

229
00:13:16,914 --> 00:13:17,915
How about this one?

230
00:13:17,915 --> 00:13:20,167
- Looks brand new.
- Nope.

231
00:13:20,167 --> 00:13:21,294
Then what about this?

232
00:13:21,294 --> 00:13:22,920
The miniature furniture set looks fancy.

233
00:13:22,920 --> 00:13:24,964
This isn't just furniture.

234
00:13:24,964 --> 00:13:26,424
Charles. Elizabeth.

235
00:13:26,424 --> 00:13:27,461
Alice.

236
00:13:27,461 --> 00:13:29,693
They're my furniture babies.

237
00:13:29,693 --> 00:13:31,298
Oh.

238
00:13:31,298 --> 00:13:32,930
- What about this?
- Are you insane?

239
00:13:32,930 --> 00:13:34,265
That's my heart.

240
00:13:34,265 --> 00:13:36,245
Then we should definitely sell it.

241
00:13:39,521 --> 00:13:41,814
This one looks kind of old.

242
00:13:41,814 --> 00:13:44,347
Hey, stop it. Put that back.

243
00:13:45,943 --> 00:13:47,862
You have an older brother?

244
00:13:47,862 --> 00:13:49,348
What?

245
00:13:52,617 --> 00:13:53,684
I'm an only child.

246
00:13:53,684 --> 00:13:56,139
And that wouldn't sell for much anyway.

247
00:13:57,538 --> 00:13:58,664
Then...

248
00:13:58,664 --> 00:14:01,132
this is the only option, right?

249
00:14:01,132 --> 00:14:03,792
We should sell something
that actually brings in money.

250
00:14:04,837 --> 00:14:07,323
Like this... Straight-on shot. One-to-one.

251
00:14:08,215 --> 00:14:09,388
Pimang.

252
00:14:09,388 --> 00:14:10,801
Look at this.

253
00:14:10,801 --> 00:14:12,608
That light just popped up.

254
00:14:14,722 --> 00:14:16,098
Thank you, Se Yeon.

255
00:14:16,098 --> 00:14:18,559
I figured you'd have it in your neighborhood.

256
00:14:18,559 --> 00:14:20,377
That's how the Pimang app works.

257
00:14:20,377 --> 00:14:22,403
Listings vary a lot by area.

258
00:14:22,403 --> 00:14:24,823
Perfect! Let's reach out right now.

259
00:14:25,592 --> 00:14:27,271
Hi, is the light still available?

260
00:14:27,271 --> 00:14:28,312
See?

261
00:14:28,312 --> 00:14:29,463
They replied right away.

262
00:14:29,463 --> 00:14:31,364
Told you I'm good.

263
00:14:31,364 --> 00:14:33,783
Wow, this woman's basically a freebie fairy.

264
00:14:33,783 --> 00:14:35,951
She doesn't buy, she doesn't sell.

265
00:14:35,951 --> 00:14:37,370
She just gives stuff away.

266
00:14:37,370 --> 00:14:39,080
Well, not a bad vibe.

267
00:14:39,080 --> 00:14:40,373
I think we'll get along.

268
00:14:40,373 --> 00:14:42,208
People like her usually don't haggle much.

269
00:14:42,208 --> 00:14:43,282
Easy, clean deal.

270
00:14:43,282 --> 00:14:45,002
We should knock off about a hundred.

271
00:14:45,002 --> 00:14:46,207
Ten percent is standard.

272
00:14:46,207 --> 00:14:47,817
Most people smile and negotiate.

273
00:14:47,817 --> 00:14:49,590
But this was listed at a million.

274
00:14:49,590 --> 00:14:51,550
You think they'll come down a hundred?

275
00:14:51,550 --> 00:14:52,609
Pimang.

276
00:14:52,609 --> 00:14:54,942
- Hi, is the light still available?
- Yes.

277
00:14:54,942 --> 00:14:56,280
Then I'd like to buy it.

278
00:14:56,280 --> 00:14:59,247
- No haggling, okay?
- I only do clean deals.

279
00:14:59,247 --> 00:15:01,514
Can we meet today?

280
00:15:01,514 --> 00:15:02,744
What time and where?

281
00:15:02,744 --> 00:15:04,577
Near Seongsu Station, at four.

282
00:15:04,577 --> 00:15:06,783
- Does that work?
- Okay.

283
00:15:09,568 --> 00:15:11,115
This time,

284
00:15:11,115 --> 00:15:14,323
I'm really gonna use every trick I've got.

285
00:15:14,323 --> 00:15:15,946
My baby...

286
00:15:16,784 --> 00:15:19,245
Your Dad's gonna ask all the right questions

287
00:15:19,245 --> 00:15:21,095
and make sure

288
00:15:21,747 --> 00:15:25,207
the place you're going to is really worth it.

289
00:16:01,370 --> 00:16:03,363
Pimang?

290
00:16:03,363 --> 00:16:05,416
Oh, yeah. You should be "CoolDealOnly," right?

291
00:16:05,416 --> 00:16:06,586
You're "TakeItAll"?

292
00:16:06,586 --> 00:16:08,072
Right.

293
00:16:14,345 --> 00:16:16,577
This is Rorman, right?

294
00:16:16,577 --> 00:16:19,054
It is, just like in the photos,
and it's in great condition.

295
00:16:19,054 --> 00:16:21,307
I take really good care of my stuff,

296
00:16:21,307 --> 00:16:23,087
so there's barely any wear.

297
00:16:25,561 --> 00:16:28,419
But you know, I only do clean deals.

298
00:16:28,419 --> 00:16:29,471
Yeah? And?

299
00:16:29,471 --> 00:16:32,050
[Round 1: Lowballing Tactic]

300
00:16:32,960 --> 00:16:35,738
Any chance there's room to negotiate?

301
00:16:35,738 --> 00:16:37,907
You said you've had it for a year.

302
00:16:37,907 --> 00:16:39,909
That makes it used, doesn't it?

303
00:16:39,909 --> 00:16:41,007
Used?

304
00:16:41,007 --> 00:16:43,649
Watch your words. My baby can hear you.

305
00:16:44,330 --> 00:16:46,373
I've taken meticulous care of it.

306
00:16:46,373 --> 00:16:49,096
At this point, it's practically vintage.

307
00:16:49,096 --> 00:16:52,046
[Round 2: Sob Story Tactic]

308
00:16:52,046 --> 00:16:54,340
I really need to buy this.

309
00:16:54,340 --> 00:16:57,802
My sister raised me from the time I was nine.

310
00:16:57,802 --> 00:16:59,240
Seriously?

311
00:16:59,853 --> 00:17:02,088
Is it a gift for her?

312
00:17:03,098 --> 00:17:04,099
Yes.

313
00:17:04,099 --> 00:17:06,496
A wedding gift.

314
00:17:07,459 --> 00:17:08,751
Yeah,

315
00:17:08,751 --> 00:17:10,356
I've heard your sob story well.

316
00:17:10,356 --> 00:17:12,024
What? A sob story?

317
00:17:12,024 --> 00:17:13,150
It's all true.

318
00:17:13,150 --> 00:17:14,318
True or not,

319
00:17:14,318 --> 00:17:16,320
I'm not interested in your family history.

320
00:17:16,320 --> 00:17:18,322
I grew up an orphan,

321
00:17:18,322 --> 00:17:21,688
so that kind of sentiment doesn't move me.

322
00:17:22,307 --> 00:17:25,412
[Round 3: Nitpicking Tactic]

323
00:17:25,412 --> 00:17:26,747
One more thing.

324
00:17:26,747 --> 00:17:28,600
This isn't a fake, right?

325
00:17:28,600 --> 00:17:30,000
A fake?

326
00:17:30,000 --> 00:17:31,794
Did you just call my baby a knockoff?

327
00:17:31,794 --> 00:17:35,214
It's wrapped up so tight I can't even see it.

328
00:17:35,214 --> 00:17:37,414
Why don't you unwrap it a bit?

329
00:17:38,717 --> 00:17:39,748
Go ahead.

330
00:17:39,748 --> 00:17:42,550
You'll see how high-end it is.

331
00:17:46,391 --> 00:17:49,414
[Final Round: Flaw-Finding Tactic]

332
00:17:53,649 --> 00:17:55,568
That's more than normal wear and tear.

333
00:17:55,568 --> 00:17:57,049
- Looks like something's on it.
- It's engraved.

334
00:17:57,049 --> 00:17:58,095
That's how the design is.

335
00:17:58,095 --> 00:17:59,131
That part's printed.

336
00:17:59,131 --> 00:18:01,528
No, forget it. Don't buy it.

337
00:18:01,528 --> 00:18:03,168
I'll take it.

338
00:18:04,201 --> 00:18:06,039
What a nightmare.

339
00:18:06,039 --> 00:18:08,027
She even brought a power cord.

340
00:18:08,637 --> 00:18:10,499
It's beautiful.

341
00:18:10,499 --> 00:18:12,126
- Could you take a picture?
- With me?

342
00:18:12,126 --> 00:18:13,419
No. Just take my picture.

343
00:18:13,419 --> 00:18:15,654
She's seriously unhinged.

344
00:18:15,654 --> 00:18:17,767
Let's just take it and get her out of here.

345
00:18:19,940 --> 00:18:23,203
Gosh, does she think she's in the photo?

346
00:18:26,664 --> 00:18:28,642
So are you buying it or not?

347
00:18:28,642 --> 00:18:30,352
I never said I wasn't.

348
00:18:30,352 --> 00:18:32,229
This is for my sister.

349
00:18:32,229 --> 00:18:33,772
It's not your sister's until you pay.

350
00:18:33,772 --> 00:18:35,997
For now, it's still mine.

351
00:18:36,854 --> 00:18:38,850
Careful with my baby.

352
00:19:01,800 --> 00:19:03,819
My baby... are you okay?

353
00:19:08,349 --> 00:19:09,892
My sister's light...

354
00:19:09,892 --> 00:19:11,443
Excuse me.

355
00:19:12,394 --> 00:19:14,550
Please leave.

356
00:19:28,577 --> 00:19:29,703
Enough.

357
00:19:29,703 --> 00:19:32,456
I don't want to deal with
a nightmare like you anymore.

358
00:19:32,456 --> 00:19:34,583
I'll just say I stepped in
something nasty, so just leave.

359
00:19:34,583 --> 00:19:36,221
Yeah, I don't want to give my sister

360
00:19:36,221 --> 00:19:38,629
a broken light as a gift either.

361
00:19:39,338 --> 00:19:40,589
She said she wanted it,

362
00:19:40,589 --> 00:19:43,075
so I was willing to buy it even broken.

363
00:19:46,831 --> 00:19:49,253
My baby, that scared you, didn't it?

364
00:19:54,811 --> 00:19:55,855
[Se Yeon]

365
00:20:01,394 --> 00:20:03,326
So are you buying it or not?

366
00:20:08,200 --> 00:20:10,760
That woman earlier was a total psycho.

367
00:20:26,021 --> 00:20:27,959
Before I report this, give me my phone back.

368
00:20:27,959 --> 00:20:29,042
Hey...

369
00:20:29,042 --> 00:20:30,973
I have my sister's family meeting tomorrow.

370
00:20:30,973 --> 00:20:32,683
My brother-in-law is a cop.

371
00:20:32,683 --> 00:20:34,184
I'm serious. I'll report you.

372
00:20:34,184 --> 00:20:36,564
So what? I'm not scared.

373
00:20:40,107 --> 00:20:41,233
- Hello...
- Hey!

374
00:20:41,233 --> 00:20:43,110
Give me my phone back.

375
00:20:43,110 --> 00:20:45,696
I don't want to get involved with you
anymore either.

376
00:20:45,696 --> 00:20:47,114
Come bring it right now.

377
00:20:47,114 --> 00:20:48,282
Where do I need to go?

378
00:20:48,282 --> 00:20:50,373
Exit 2 at Seongsu Station,
the same place as earlier.

379
00:20:51,076 --> 00:20:53,412
That's a three-hour round trip.

380
00:20:53,412 --> 00:20:54,980
Then I'll come tomorrow.

381
00:20:54,980 --> 00:20:57,866
Around five, after my sister's family meeting.

382
00:21:07,634 --> 00:21:10,388
[Family of Groom Sun Woo Jin
and Bride Woo Hyun Joo]

383
00:21:13,062 --> 00:21:15,462
[Groom Sun Woo Jin,
Bride Woo Hyun Joo's family]

384
00:21:18,145 --> 00:21:19,605
Brother.

385
00:21:20,795 --> 00:21:23,197
Brother!

386
00:21:23,859 --> 00:21:25,760
Don't go.

387
00:21:27,362 --> 00:21:29,014
Brother...

388
00:21:31,158 --> 00:21:33,944
Wow, look at all these side dishes.

389
00:21:34,661 --> 00:21:37,206
How did you even book a place like this?

390
00:21:37,206 --> 00:21:38,707
It's a proper family meeting.

391
00:21:38,707 --> 00:21:41,575
I've got to splurge a little
for something like this.

392
00:21:41,575 --> 00:21:42,878
Help yourself.

393
00:21:42,878 --> 00:21:44,379
It's on me.

394
00:21:44,379 --> 00:21:45,923
Dig in,

395
00:21:45,923 --> 00:21:47,966
and let's really get this meeting started.

396
00:21:47,966 --> 00:21:49,093
I'll pay.

397
00:21:49,093 --> 00:21:50,126
Don't.

398
00:21:50,126 --> 00:21:51,723
We've technically got one more person,

399
00:21:51,723 --> 00:21:53,138
so I'll cover it.

400
00:21:53,138 --> 00:21:54,515
Go ahead and eat.

401
00:21:54,515 --> 00:21:56,553
Hyun Joo, try this.

402
00:21:56,553 --> 00:21:58,727
They say the marinated crab here is amazing.

403
00:21:58,727 --> 00:22:00,418
- Really?
- Yeah.

404
00:22:00,418 --> 00:22:02,528
I already checked the blogs...

405
00:22:03,148 --> 00:22:04,818
Oh, right.

406
00:22:04,818 --> 00:22:05,867
Woo Jin!

407
00:22:05,867 --> 00:22:07,351
What is it?

408
00:22:13,534 --> 00:22:15,327
Pimang guy?

409
00:22:15,327 --> 00:22:17,119
Sorry I'm late.

410
00:22:17,853 --> 00:22:20,570
I got the invitation
pretty last minute yesterday.

411
00:22:20,570 --> 00:22:22,388
Why are you sitting here?

412
00:22:22,388 --> 00:22:24,215
What are you doing
at someone else's family event?

413
00:22:24,215 --> 00:22:25,865
Long time no see.

414
00:22:26,828 --> 00:22:28,340
Bro.

415
00:22:29,591 --> 00:22:32,136
How many years has it been, bro?

416
00:22:32,136 --> 00:22:33,969
- Brother?
- Huh?

417
00:22:38,267 --> 00:22:39,444
So I guess now

418
00:22:39,444 --> 00:22:41,523
I should call you my in-law.

419
00:22:42,146 --> 00:22:43,940
Let's eat.

420
00:22:50,279 --> 00:22:52,492
You picked a great place.

421
00:22:53,474 --> 00:22:55,434
Marinated crab is my favorite.

422
00:22:57,161 --> 00:22:59,255
Have some abalone.

423
00:23:00,828 --> 00:23:01,999
This is so good.

424
00:23:01,999 --> 00:23:04,418
Definitely wild-caught.

425
00:23:04,418 --> 00:23:06,170
Looks like we have a lot in common.

426
00:23:06,170 --> 00:23:07,421
This place too.

427
00:23:07,421 --> 00:23:10,235
You really know my taste, my dear in-law.

428
00:23:19,725 --> 00:23:20,779
Hey.

429
00:23:20,779 --> 00:23:22,911
Can we talk for a minute?

430
00:23:25,189 --> 00:23:27,340
If you want.

431
00:23:28,192 --> 00:23:30,306
Oh, right.

432
00:23:30,306 --> 00:23:32,946
I never said thank you.

433
00:23:32,946 --> 00:23:34,531
Thank you.

434
00:23:34,531 --> 00:23:35,866
Because of you,

435
00:23:35,866 --> 00:23:38,285
I get to see my brother again
after all these years.

436
00:23:38,285 --> 00:23:39,328
But yesterday,

437
00:23:39,328 --> 00:23:41,997
didn't you say you were an orphan?

438
00:23:41,997 --> 00:23:44,107
Like you heard earlier,

439
00:23:44,107 --> 00:23:47,586
it's been a very long time since we reunited.

440
00:23:47,586 --> 00:23:50,270
So you really are Woo Jin's brother?

441
00:23:50,270 --> 00:23:52,841
I've never heard about you.

442
00:23:52,841 --> 00:23:55,734
Woo Jin said there wouldn't be
any family on his side today.

443
00:23:57,137 --> 00:24:00,248
Oh, so that's what my brother said.

444
00:24:01,433 --> 00:24:03,099
I get it.

445
00:24:10,268 --> 00:24:11,443
Woo Jin.

446
00:24:11,443 --> 00:24:12,778
Huh?

447
00:24:12,778 --> 00:24:15,778
He's the brother you mentioned before, right?

448
00:24:17,199 --> 00:24:18,685
Yeah.

449
00:24:22,265 --> 00:24:26,124
I think I need to talk to Tae Hyung first.

450
00:24:26,124 --> 00:24:27,539
Okay.

451
00:24:31,254 --> 00:24:32,878
[Woo Hyun Joo, Woo Hyun Jin, Woo Jin]

452
00:24:32,878 --> 00:24:35,278
[Our Family]

453
00:24:42,975 --> 00:24:45,894
May I call you Tae Hyung?

454
00:24:45,894 --> 00:24:48,381
What do you do for a living, Tae Hyung?

455
00:24:49,815 --> 00:24:51,519
Bro.

456
00:24:51,519 --> 00:24:53,297
Do you know what I do?

457
00:25:01,702 --> 00:25:04,123
I'm a photographer.

458
00:25:04,123 --> 00:25:05,388
Oh.

459
00:25:05,388 --> 00:25:07,788
So you're in the arts.

460
00:25:08,583 --> 00:25:10,294
That's a wonderful line of work.

461
00:25:10,294 --> 00:25:12,278
And how old are you?

462
00:25:14,819 --> 00:25:16,752
Seriously...

463
00:25:18,885 --> 00:25:21,671
So it's true.
You really never told her about me.

464
00:25:23,224 --> 00:25:24,433
Tae Hyung, let's step outside.

465
00:25:24,433 --> 00:25:25,767
I need to talk to you first.

466
00:25:25,767 --> 00:25:27,306
Why?

467
00:25:27,978 --> 00:25:30,571
Afraid I'll tell her
you dumped me at an orphanage?

468
00:25:31,898 --> 00:25:33,591
Did you know that?

469
00:25:34,192 --> 00:25:35,593
He is...

470
00:25:36,808 --> 00:25:38,735
really good at abandoning people.

471
00:25:41,457 --> 00:25:43,025
When things get hard,

472
00:25:43,952 --> 00:25:46,638
he's the kind of person
who throws away family first.

473
00:25:48,373 --> 00:25:50,099
So don't trust him too much.

474
00:26:08,060 --> 00:26:09,526
Woo Jin...

475
00:26:17,319 --> 00:26:18,958
Tae Hyung.

476
00:26:18,958 --> 00:26:20,504
Sun Tae Hyung!

477
00:26:24,910 --> 00:26:26,078
Let's talk.

478
00:26:26,078 --> 00:26:27,960
About what?

479
00:26:27,960 --> 00:26:31,086
What, here to say
you should've left me for good?

480
00:26:34,586 --> 00:26:36,713
Hey.

481
00:26:36,713 --> 00:26:38,973
Do you know why I started photography?

482
00:26:40,926 --> 00:26:43,136
I did it because of you.

483
00:26:43,136 --> 00:26:46,723
The last birthday present you ever gave me.

484
00:26:46,723 --> 00:26:48,369
You remember, right?

485
00:26:49,684 --> 00:26:50,977
You handed me that one thing

486
00:26:50,977 --> 00:26:52,170
and then you walked away.

487
00:26:52,170 --> 00:26:55,350
I believed your stupid lies,
and this is where it got me.

488
00:27:02,786 --> 00:27:03,949
From that moment on,

489
00:27:03,949 --> 00:27:06,284
you already erased me from your life.

490
00:27:06,284 --> 00:27:08,645
You were ready to start a new family.

491
00:27:09,413 --> 00:27:12,130
And I showed up here anyway,
without taking the hint.

492
00:27:14,028 --> 00:27:16,341
What I thought I was coming here for...

493
00:27:23,254 --> 00:27:25,280
I'm not waiting for you anymore.

494
00:27:27,514 --> 00:27:29,068
This time,

495
00:27:31,474 --> 00:27:33,167
I'm the one leaving you.

496
00:27:36,606 --> 00:27:39,146
I can't even bring myself to wish you well.

497
00:27:42,334 --> 00:27:44,656
Let's never see each other again.

498
00:27:44,656 --> 00:27:46,075
Sun Woo Jin.

499
00:28:26,788 --> 00:28:27,881
Woo Jin.

500
00:28:27,881 --> 00:28:30,181
Can I really buy anything?

501
00:28:49,554 --> 00:28:51,311
Okay, hold still.

502
00:28:56,436 --> 00:28:57,796
Happy birthday, Tae Hyung.

503
00:28:57,796 --> 00:29:00,091
I wish it could be my birthday every day.

504
00:29:00,899 --> 00:29:02,067
Do you like the shoes?

505
00:29:02,067 --> 00:29:03,520
Yeah.

506
00:29:10,472 --> 00:29:14,276
[Moonlight Children's Home]

507
00:29:26,546 --> 00:29:28,052
Brother...

508
00:29:29,135 --> 00:29:30,718
When the rain stops,

509
00:29:31,304 --> 00:29:32,914
I'll come get you.

510
00:29:34,975 --> 00:29:36,376
Wait for me.

511
00:29:37,686 --> 00:29:39,087
Bro...

512
00:29:40,855 --> 00:29:43,942
Brother!

513
00:29:43,942 --> 00:29:45,802
Don't go.

514
00:29:47,320 --> 00:29:49,055
Bro...

515
00:30:53,011 --> 00:30:55,388
Next, the bride and groom
would like to greet...

516
00:30:55,388 --> 00:30:57,932
I guess he never came.

517
00:30:57,932 --> 00:30:59,424
Who?

518
00:30:59,424 --> 00:31:01,764
No, nothing.

519
00:31:06,900 --> 00:31:08,711
Now we'll take photos

520
00:31:08,711 --> 00:31:10,111
with the families of the bride and groom.

521
00:31:10,111 --> 00:31:11,686
Please come forward.

522
00:31:25,334 --> 00:31:26,994
[Three Years Later]

523
00:31:48,108 --> 00:31:49,651
Hello.

524
00:31:49,651 --> 00:31:51,277
- Hi.
- Morning, Hyun Jin.

525
00:31:51,277 --> 00:31:53,346
You're early again today.

526
00:31:58,284 --> 00:31:59,684
[Woo Hyun Jin]

527
00:32:02,038 --> 00:32:03,081
What if we go with

528
00:32:03,081 --> 00:32:04,354
a brighter tone overall?

529
00:32:04,354 --> 00:32:05,834
- Grab some coffee first.
- Thank you.

530
00:32:05,834 --> 00:32:07,374
- Latte?
- Here you go.

531
00:32:08,211 --> 00:32:09,904
Our ambitious

532
00:32:11,005 --> 00:32:14,008
Hirre Limited Drop live campaign.

533
00:32:14,008 --> 00:32:16,094
This is finally my place.

534
00:32:16,094 --> 00:32:18,256
I can actually

535
00:32:18,256 --> 00:32:20,556
put nails in the wall now.

536
00:32:20,556 --> 00:32:22,362
Honestly, I should've quit photography

537
00:32:22,362 --> 00:32:24,060
and followed you three years ago.

538
00:32:24,060 --> 00:32:25,658
I'm still just an assistant,

539
00:32:25,658 --> 00:32:28,022
and you bought an apartment.
Does that even make sense?

540
00:32:28,022 --> 00:32:29,674
Fourteen pyeong?

541
00:32:29,674 --> 00:32:32,785
You freelancers wouldn't get it.

542
00:32:33,820 --> 00:32:35,405
Having a loan approved

543
00:32:35,405 --> 00:32:36,656
and full benefits

544
00:32:36,656 --> 00:32:38,616
is a huge deal.

545
00:32:38,616 --> 00:32:41,286
So you're really not going back to photography?

546
00:32:41,286 --> 00:32:43,832
You always said style is everything.

547
00:32:51,055 --> 00:32:53,095
Turns out style doesn't keep you alive.

548
00:32:54,632 --> 00:32:57,844
And there's no one left to show it to anyway.

549
00:32:57,844 --> 00:32:59,804
Who?

550
00:32:59,804 --> 00:33:01,931
Hey, I'll put a shelf here.

551
00:33:01,931 --> 00:33:03,789
Display my collection here.

552
00:33:03,789 --> 00:33:05,769
Might as well splurge on a couch too.

553
00:33:05,769 --> 00:33:07,029
That's painfully boring.

554
00:33:07,029 --> 00:33:08,646
This responsible, planned-out version of you

555
00:33:08,646 --> 00:33:10,129
is not the guy I knew.

556
00:33:10,129 --> 00:33:11,382
Definitely not my role model.

557
00:33:11,382 --> 00:33:13,607
Hey, don't chase people.

558
00:33:13,607 --> 00:33:14,944
Chase real estate.

559
00:33:14,944 --> 00:33:17,447
People only disappoint you.

560
00:33:17,447 --> 00:33:19,073
This place and my money

561
00:33:19,073 --> 00:33:21,951
will never betray me.

562
00:33:21,951 --> 00:33:23,456
Look.

563
00:33:24,496 --> 00:33:27,165
This is the perfect single life.

564
00:33:27,165 --> 00:33:28,458
Cut everything off,

565
00:33:28,458 --> 00:33:30,651
and it's smooth sailing.

566
00:33:34,422 --> 00:33:35,865
Nice view.

567
00:33:38,300 --> 00:33:40,847
[Personnel Assignment Notice]
[Woo Hyun Jin - Pending]

568
00:33:43,014 --> 00:33:46,307
Why am I the only one...

569
00:33:46,307 --> 00:33:49,340
Look, I know you've been working hard.

570
00:33:49,340 --> 00:33:50,375
But

571
00:33:50,375 --> 00:33:52,315
working hard alone isn't always enough.

572
00:33:52,315 --> 00:33:55,092
You went to a good university,
your grades are solid.

573
00:33:55,092 --> 00:33:56,236
But...

574
00:33:56,236 --> 00:33:58,029
so is everyone else.

575
00:33:58,029 --> 00:34:00,889
That's why you need something extra.

576
00:34:00,889 --> 00:34:02,298
These days,

577
00:34:02,298 --> 00:34:03,633
even credentials

578
00:34:03,633 --> 00:34:05,676
are something you buy with money.

579
00:34:18,347 --> 00:34:22,069
Why is it so hard just to pull my own weight?

580
00:34:25,976 --> 00:34:28,623
What am I supposed to tell Hyun Joo this time?

581
00:34:32,730 --> 00:34:34,325
[My dear sister]

582
00:34:53,418 --> 00:34:55,962
Why did you make so much?

583
00:34:55,962 --> 00:34:57,589
This is exactly what I've been craving.

584
00:34:57,589 --> 00:34:58,882
Your japchae.

585
00:34:58,882 --> 00:35:00,752
There's tteokbokki too?

586
00:35:00,752 --> 00:35:01,843
Yay!

587
00:35:01,843 --> 00:35:03,219
You know,

588
00:35:03,219 --> 00:35:05,972
that place keeps putting perilla leaves
in their tteokbokki.

589
00:35:05,972 --> 00:35:08,225
I don't like it.

590
00:35:08,225 --> 00:35:09,436
Living on my own

591
00:35:09,436 --> 00:35:10,823
made me realize home cooking is the best.

592
00:35:10,823 --> 00:35:13,271
Are you eating properly?

593
00:35:13,271 --> 00:35:15,197
Why do you keep losing weight?

594
00:35:16,733 --> 00:35:17,901
No, I gained weight.

595
00:35:17,901 --> 00:35:20,862
My company cafeteria is actually great.

596
00:35:20,862 --> 00:35:22,614
They serve a good balance
of protein, carbs, and fat,

597
00:35:22,614 --> 00:35:23,803
so don't worry.

598
00:35:23,803 --> 00:35:25,742
Being full-time really is different.

599
00:35:25,742 --> 00:35:28,453
I'm exhausted from all the overtime.

600
00:35:28,453 --> 00:35:29,954
That's probably why

601
00:35:29,954 --> 00:35:31,474
I haven't been able to reach you lately.

602
00:35:31,474 --> 00:35:32,967
Sorry.

603
00:35:36,085 --> 00:35:37,945
Come up to Seoul now.

604
00:35:38,796 --> 00:35:41,507
While I was organizing my place,

605
00:35:41,507 --> 00:35:46,054
I found all your old materials
from when you were applying to BS.

606
00:35:46,054 --> 00:35:48,974
Use your major and apply again.

607
00:35:51,409 --> 00:35:52,852
What are you talking about?

608
00:35:52,852 --> 00:35:53,937
I mean...

609
00:35:53,937 --> 00:35:56,547
I'm in a better place now.

610
00:35:57,607 --> 00:35:59,020
So

611
00:35:59,734 --> 00:36:01,635
you can slow down too.

612
00:36:02,286 --> 00:36:04,621
You've been running nonstop all this time.

613
00:36:04,621 --> 00:36:08,201
If you keep pushing like that,
you're going to burn out.

614
00:36:08,201 --> 00:36:10,078
Hyun Jin.

615
00:36:10,078 --> 00:36:11,545
Come home.

616
00:36:11,545 --> 00:36:14,431
This time, I'll support you properly.

617
00:36:17,796 --> 00:36:20,262
I'm going to the bathroom for a second.

618
00:36:47,448 --> 00:36:49,683
[How to Write a Strong Personal Statement]

619
00:36:49,683 --> 00:36:52,349
[The Real Guide to Getting a Job]

620
00:36:57,583 --> 00:36:58,793
Hyun Jin.

621
00:36:58,793 --> 00:37:01,259
You want me to move in here?

622
00:37:01,259 --> 00:37:03,423
When did you find out

623
00:37:03,423 --> 00:37:05,269
I didn't get picked for full-time?

624
00:37:09,387 --> 00:37:12,098
Why do you always make me feel like an idiot?

625
00:37:12,098 --> 00:37:14,392
Every time you do this,

626
00:37:14,392 --> 00:37:16,269
because of you,

627
00:37:16,269 --> 00:37:18,462
I end up hating myself.

628
00:37:19,272 --> 00:37:20,732
What are you talking about?

629
00:37:20,732 --> 00:37:23,651
You still think I can't pull my own weight.

630
00:37:23,651 --> 00:37:26,016
That's why you made me a room, right?

631
00:37:26,016 --> 00:37:29,323
Do you really have to turn me
into some kind of burden?

632
00:37:29,323 --> 00:37:30,693
How are you a burden?

633
00:37:30,693 --> 00:37:32,526
I am.

634
00:37:32,526 --> 00:37:35,006
Like this thing stuck to you,
weighing you down.

635
00:37:36,372 --> 00:37:37,707
Hyun Jin.

636
00:37:37,707 --> 00:37:39,500
It's too much for me.

637
00:37:39,500 --> 00:37:41,502
Sometimes,

638
00:37:41,502 --> 00:37:43,755
honestly wish I were on my own.

639
00:37:43,755 --> 00:37:45,256
Not Woo Hyun Joo's sister.

640
00:37:45,256 --> 00:37:46,966
Just Woo Hyun Jin.

641
00:37:46,966 --> 00:37:48,593
Woo Hyun Jin.

642
00:37:48,593 --> 00:37:50,261
Don't say something you'll regret.

643
00:37:50,261 --> 00:37:52,013
I won't.

644
00:37:52,013 --> 00:37:54,098
I'm never moving into this house.

645
00:37:54,098 --> 00:37:55,708
So please...

646
00:37:58,534 --> 00:38:00,500
Just leave me alone.

647
00:38:17,622 --> 00:38:20,615
I was so stupid,
letting my pride ruin everything.

648
00:38:21,225 --> 00:38:23,835
You're the worst, Woo Hyun Jin.

649
00:38:23,835 --> 00:38:25,471
[Myeongin Police Station]

650
00:38:26,922 --> 00:38:28,549
[Yangseong Police Substation]

651
00:38:28,549 --> 00:38:30,822
Still haven't heard from your sister?

652
00:38:32,178 --> 00:38:34,055
She's been off the grid for days.

653
00:38:34,055 --> 00:38:35,873
Guess she's really hurt.

654
00:38:37,183 --> 00:38:39,519
She'll call by tonight.

655
00:38:39,519 --> 00:38:41,395
You two always fight like this,

656
00:38:41,395 --> 00:38:43,681
then make up like nothing happened.

657
00:38:45,233 --> 00:38:46,426
Yeah, I'm on my way.

658
00:38:46,426 --> 00:38:48,152
About twenty minutes.

659
00:38:48,152 --> 00:38:49,177
Okay.

660
00:38:49,177 --> 00:38:51,083
See you soon.

661
00:38:52,156 --> 00:38:55,256
Oh, your anniversary?

662
00:38:55,256 --> 00:38:57,453
You taking her somewhere nice tonight?

663
00:38:57,453 --> 00:38:58,996
Are you jealous?

664
00:38:58,996 --> 00:39:00,757
Of course I am.

665
00:39:00,757 --> 00:39:02,451
Get back to work.

666
00:39:03,292 --> 00:39:04,335
- Bye.
- Bye.

667
00:39:04,335 --> 00:39:05,705
- Hang in there.
- Yeah.

668
00:39:05,705 --> 00:39:06,902
- Have a wonderful night.
- Thanks.

669
00:39:06,902 --> 00:39:08,778
Bye.

670
00:39:08,778 --> 00:39:11,104
You should get married soon too.

671
00:39:18,959 --> 00:39:22,673
[Woo Jin, your father's being released
on parole as a model inmate on June 1.]

672
00:39:35,468 --> 00:39:36,868
[Tae Hyung]

673
00:39:42,873 --> 00:39:44,846
[Tae Hyung]

674
00:40:02,389 --> 00:40:04,209
[Please pick up. I'm worried.]

675
00:40:05,093 --> 00:40:07,590
Still no word from her.

676
00:40:11,652 --> 00:40:13,399
Woo Jin.

677
00:40:13,399 --> 00:40:15,448
What are you thinking about?

678
00:40:15,448 --> 00:40:16,908
Huh?

679
00:40:16,908 --> 00:40:18,566
Is something wrong?

680
00:40:19,896 --> 00:40:21,735
No, it's nothing.

681
00:40:24,957 --> 00:40:26,561
Is this about Tae Hyung?

682
00:40:28,669 --> 00:40:31,495
You always get like this
when his name comes up.

683
00:40:33,007 --> 00:40:36,393
You still can't tell me everything, can you?

684
00:40:41,724 --> 00:40:43,283
Actually, he is...

685
00:41:11,545 --> 00:41:14,970
[Full-Time Conversion Results]
[BS Food Document Screening Results]

686
00:41:17,342 --> 00:41:18,135
[2025 BS FOOD Application Status]

687
00:41:18,135 --> 00:41:20,048
[Your documents have been
successfully submitted.]

688
00:41:36,869 --> 00:41:38,587
[Moving into My Own Place!]

689
00:41:47,665 --> 00:41:49,625
Hello?

690
00:41:49,625 --> 00:41:51,185
Yes, hello?

691
00:42:14,998 --> 00:42:16,767
Sister.

692
00:42:16,767 --> 00:42:18,961
You're my favorite person in the whole world.

693
00:42:18,961 --> 00:42:19,989
Really?

694
00:42:19,989 --> 00:42:21,032
What about you?

695
00:42:21,032 --> 00:42:24,143
You're my favorite too. In the whole world.

696
00:42:33,252 --> 00:42:34,337
Brother.

697
00:42:34,337 --> 00:42:36,255
When are you coming?

698
00:42:36,255 --> 00:42:38,657
You said you'd come when the rain stops.

699
00:42:39,342 --> 00:42:42,219
How many nights do I have to sleep?

700
00:42:42,219 --> 00:42:43,721
Ten nights?

701
00:42:43,721 --> 00:42:45,288
A hundred nights?

702
00:42:46,515 --> 00:42:48,726
After you sleep for a hundred nights

703
00:42:48,726 --> 00:42:50,381
and grow a little more,

704
00:42:51,062 --> 00:42:52,955
I'll come get you.

705
00:42:53,814 --> 00:42:55,507
I'm not waiting for you anymore.

706
00:42:56,124 --> 00:42:57,665
This time,

707
00:42:58,493 --> 00:43:00,267
I'm the one leaving you.

708
00:43:01,391 --> 00:43:03,240
Let's never see each other again.

709
00:43:03,240 --> 00:43:04,686
Sun Woo Jin.

710
00:43:05,743 --> 00:43:07,356
I'll come...

711
00:43:08,788 --> 00:43:10,476
get you.

712
00:43:37,373 --> 00:43:40,393
Do you really have to turn me
into some kind of burden?

713
00:43:41,529 --> 00:43:43,430
How are you a burden?

714
00:43:45,741 --> 00:43:47,410
Sometimes,

715
00:43:47,410 --> 00:43:49,620
honestly wish I were on my own.

716
00:43:49,620 --> 00:43:51,038
Not Woo Hyun Joo's sister.

717
00:43:51,038 --> 00:43:52,981
Just Woo Hyun Jin.

718
00:43:55,292 --> 00:43:58,070
That was all a lie.

719
00:44:02,403 --> 00:44:05,269
How could you go, believing just that?

720
00:44:08,514 --> 00:44:11,080
I didn't mean it.

721
00:45:31,597 --> 00:45:33,094
Mommy?

722
00:45:42,399 --> 00:45:43,800
[Funeral Hall]

723
00:45:43,800 --> 00:45:44,979
Where's that sound coming from?

724
00:45:44,979 --> 00:45:46,028
I think it's next door.

725
00:45:46,028 --> 00:45:47,571
Why is that baby crying so much?

726
00:45:47,571 --> 00:45:49,907
Is that the baby who survived alone?

727
00:45:49,907 --> 00:45:51,367
That's heartbreaking.

728
00:45:51,367 --> 00:45:52,938
Are you hungry?

729
00:45:52,938 --> 00:45:54,286
Did you pee?

730
00:45:54,286 --> 00:45:55,932
Why are you crying?

731
00:45:56,957 --> 00:45:58,526
Mommy.

732
00:45:59,542 --> 00:46:00,960
Are you sick?

733
00:46:00,960 --> 00:46:03,504
It's okay, it's okay.

734
00:46:03,504 --> 00:46:04,950
Don't cry.

735
00:46:05,631 --> 00:46:07,123
Good boy.

736
00:46:09,642 --> 00:46:11,428
Why? What's wrong?

737
00:46:12,396 --> 00:46:14,335
Wait, wait.

738
00:46:18,561 --> 00:46:20,387
Mommy.

739
00:46:21,772 --> 00:46:23,338
Woo Joo.

740
00:46:28,835 --> 00:46:30,337
What...

741
00:46:41,161 --> 00:46:42,214
Are you okay?

742
00:46:42,214 --> 00:46:43,419
You look hurt.

743
00:46:43,419 --> 00:46:44,503
You should go to the hospital.

744
00:46:44,503 --> 00:46:45,629
Move slowly.

745
00:46:45,629 --> 00:46:47,642
You really should get checked.

746
00:46:48,424 --> 00:46:50,350
Don't move. Stay still.

747
00:47:25,215 --> 00:47:26,728
Woo Jin.

748
00:47:32,551 --> 00:47:34,619
I'm going to erase you

749
00:47:38,182 --> 00:47:39,916
from my life now.

750
00:47:43,843 --> 00:47:45,161
Chief mourner,

751
00:47:45,161 --> 00:47:47,076
you have visitors.

752
00:48:04,868 --> 00:48:06,795
Senior Officer Sun

753
00:48:07,419 --> 00:48:10,172
was truly a good person.

754
00:48:10,172 --> 00:48:13,884
He always looked out for us juniors too.

755
00:48:13,884 --> 00:48:15,470
He really was...

756
00:48:16,720 --> 00:48:19,226
a great senior.

757
00:48:43,472 --> 00:48:45,582
[Funeral Hall Meal Options]
Will it be yukgaejang?

758
00:48:45,582 --> 00:48:47,762
Or radish beef soup?

759
00:48:50,754 --> 00:48:53,514
The real chief mourner says to go with this.

760
00:48:54,425 --> 00:48:57,369
Then thirty servings? Fifty?

761
00:48:58,345 --> 00:49:00,118
He's saying a hundred.

762
00:49:01,056 --> 00:49:02,544
Chief mourner.

763
00:49:03,539 --> 00:49:04,806
Please take a look at this too.

764
00:49:04,806 --> 00:49:06,409
Burial clothes?

765
00:49:07,062 --> 00:49:08,098
Option one.

766
00:49:08,098 --> 00:49:09,523
Coffin type?

767
00:49:09,523 --> 00:49:10,547
Option one.

768
00:49:10,547 --> 00:49:11,900
Burial site?

769
00:49:11,900 --> 00:49:12,901
Urn?

770
00:49:12,901 --> 00:49:14,027
Just option one.

771
00:49:14,027 --> 00:49:16,240
Please make everything option one.

772
00:49:24,329 --> 00:49:25,789
What?

773
00:49:25,789 --> 00:49:27,858
Just go.

774
00:50:02,451 --> 00:50:04,737
What am I supposed to do with you?

775
00:50:06,538 --> 00:50:08,258
You want more?

776
00:50:23,388 --> 00:50:24,719
That's gross.

777
00:50:24,719 --> 00:50:26,173
Don't come here.

778
00:50:26,809 --> 00:50:28,116
Mommy.

779
00:50:28,116 --> 00:50:29,353
Go back and sleep.

780
00:50:29,353 --> 00:50:31,493
Stop getting in the way.

781
00:50:32,979 --> 00:50:35,025
When is your aunt coming, seriously?

782
00:50:35,025 --> 00:50:36,026
Hey, hey.

783
00:50:36,026 --> 00:50:37,844
Don't come to me.

784
00:50:39,662 --> 00:50:40,772
Stop!

785
00:50:40,772 --> 00:50:42,338
Wait.

786
00:50:46,537 --> 00:50:48,737
Why are you so heavy?

787
00:50:48,737 --> 00:50:50,916
Is it all poop or what?

788
00:50:50,916 --> 00:50:52,417
Mommy.

789
00:50:52,417 --> 00:50:54,645
Did you even eat today...

790
00:50:56,181 --> 00:50:57,965
Hey?

791
00:50:57,965 --> 00:50:59,534
Hey, stop.

792
00:50:59,534 --> 00:51:01,134
What are you doing?

793
00:51:01,134 --> 00:51:02,469
Hey.

794
00:51:02,469 --> 00:51:04,037
Hey, hey!

795
00:51:11,937 --> 00:51:13,939
Sun Tae Hyung...

796
00:51:13,939 --> 00:51:15,984
Why the hell are you here,

797
00:51:15,984 --> 00:51:18,944
letting yourself end up like this?

798
00:51:18,944 --> 00:51:20,112
Hey.

799
00:51:20,112 --> 00:51:22,447
Why isn't your aunt here yet?

800
00:51:22,447 --> 00:51:23,740
When she shows up,

801
00:51:23,740 --> 00:51:25,185
I'm charging her for everything.

802
00:51:25,185 --> 00:51:27,870
From making me chief mourner
to all this hand washing.

803
00:51:29,032 --> 00:51:31,305
What? You smiling?

804
00:51:31,305 --> 00:51:32,581
This is not the time to smile.

805
00:51:32,581 --> 00:51:34,330
Read the room.

806
00:51:38,491 --> 00:51:41,143
Why is she taking so long?

807
00:51:41,143 --> 00:51:42,217
What's that?

808
00:51:42,217 --> 00:51:44,261
Why did he put the baby there?

809
00:51:44,261 --> 00:51:45,679
Oh my, look at that baby.

810
00:51:45,679 --> 00:51:46,930
What is that?

811
00:51:46,930 --> 00:51:48,498
Is that a baby?

812
00:52:00,080 --> 00:52:02,120
What's that?

813
00:52:02,120 --> 00:52:05,194
I sprained a ligament,
so I have to be in a cast for two weeks.

814
00:52:11,209 --> 00:52:12,789
Gosh...

815
00:52:12,789 --> 00:52:14,291
Wasn't that from the bathroom?

816
00:52:14,291 --> 00:52:15,584
Why did you...

817
00:52:15,584 --> 00:52:17,990
Why did you just leave the baby with me?

818
00:52:20,923 --> 00:52:22,449
Come on. Let's go.

819
00:52:26,975 --> 00:52:28,639
Just leave him.

820
00:52:28,639 --> 00:52:30,206
I'll do it.

821
00:53:00,101 --> 00:53:01,560
Hyun Jin.

822
00:53:19,594 --> 00:53:20,720
Why aren't you eating?

823
00:53:20,720 --> 00:53:22,261
Go on, eat.

824
00:53:25,195 --> 00:53:27,128
This is really hard on you, isn't it?

825
00:53:31,868 --> 00:53:33,394
Yeah.

826
00:53:34,413 --> 00:53:35,872
Still...

827
00:53:35,872 --> 00:53:39,543
it's a little easier not having to stand
as chief mourner alone.

828
00:53:39,543 --> 00:53:41,169
Is that the in-law you mentioned before?

829
00:53:41,169 --> 00:53:43,040
- The Pimang guy?
- Yeah.

830
00:53:46,091 --> 00:53:47,951
Has he been helping a lot?

831
00:53:48,552 --> 00:53:49,594
Yeah.

832
00:53:49,594 --> 00:53:51,304
When I got back from the hospital,

833
00:53:51,304 --> 00:53:55,017
he'd already picked out
the burial clothes and the urn.

834
00:53:55,017 --> 00:53:57,310
He even chose my sister's coffin.

835
00:53:57,310 --> 00:53:59,563
I don't really know any of this stuff.

836
00:53:59,563 --> 00:54:01,756
I guess that's a relief, right?

837
00:54:01,756 --> 00:54:02,808
Oh, right.

838
00:54:02,808 --> 00:54:04,818
Why is your arm hurt all of a sudden?

839
00:54:04,818 --> 00:54:06,445
That too...

840
00:54:06,445 --> 00:54:08,321
because of him.

841
00:54:08,321 --> 00:54:11,324
I got a cast as soon as
I came to the funeral hall,

842
00:54:11,324 --> 00:54:12,981
my arm hurts,

843
00:54:14,174 --> 00:54:16,212
my head's all over the place.

844
00:54:16,212 --> 00:54:17,992
None of this feels real.

845
00:54:20,459 --> 00:54:23,153
You're not okay at all.

846
00:54:24,376 --> 00:54:25,777
It's just...

847
00:54:27,090 --> 00:54:29,784
I can't believe my sister is

848
00:54:30,635 --> 00:54:32,488
in that memorial photo.

849
00:54:34,014 --> 00:54:37,434
It feels like if I went home right now,

850
00:54:37,434 --> 00:54:38,924
she'd be there.

851
00:54:40,437 --> 00:54:42,213
Maybe that's why.

852
00:54:42,856 --> 00:54:44,749
It just doesn't feel real.

853
00:56:19,828 --> 00:56:21,104
As you know,

854
00:56:21,104 --> 00:56:23,957
Woo Joo currently has no legal guardian.

855
00:56:23,957 --> 00:56:27,622
If neither of you is willing to take him in,

856
00:56:27,622 --> 00:56:29,928
he'll be placed in a care facility.

857
00:56:30,655 --> 00:56:31,907
Since

858
00:56:31,907 --> 00:56:35,810
you're both his closest relatives,

859
00:56:35,810 --> 00:56:39,084
we need to decide which of you will raise him.

860
00:56:40,932 --> 00:56:43,602
So now you're asking me this too?

861
00:56:43,602 --> 00:56:45,979
I just spent three days deciding
whether to serve thirty portions of yukgaejang,

862
00:56:45,979 --> 00:56:48,162
whether the burial clothes
should be hemp or a cotton blend,

863
00:56:48,162 --> 00:56:50,460
even the shape of the coffin handles

864
00:56:50,460 --> 00:56:52,235
and the thank-you gifts for mourners.

865
00:56:52,235 --> 00:56:53,653
I answered all of that.

866
00:56:53,653 --> 00:56:55,313
But why are you asking me about a kid?

867
00:56:55,313 --> 00:56:57,715
I only met him for the first time here.

868
00:56:59,910 --> 00:57:02,704
I'm not someone
who can take responsibility for anyone.

869
00:57:02,704 --> 00:57:05,917
And I'm done being involved with Sun Woo Jin.

870
00:57:34,069 --> 00:57:35,808
I'll raise him.

871
00:57:35,808 --> 00:57:37,762
I'll take care of Woo Joo.

872
00:58:03,640 --> 00:58:06,226
This is the last thing I'll do.

873
00:58:06,226 --> 00:58:08,319
Let's not see each other again.

874
00:58:08,910 --> 00:58:11,243
I don't expect we'll ever be involved again.

875
00:58:12,018 --> 00:58:13,441
Take care.

876
00:58:13,441 --> 00:58:15,321
And raise the kid well.

877
00:58:16,194 --> 00:58:18,214
I hope you recover soon.

878
00:58:19,364 --> 00:58:21,030
Hey, little one.

879
00:58:21,638 --> 00:58:23,748
Let's never see each other again.

880
00:58:27,539 --> 00:58:29,912
Here. This is my last gift.

881
00:58:45,274 --> 00:58:46,933
Woo Joo,

882
00:58:46,933 --> 00:58:48,659
Let's go home.

883
00:59:30,619 --> 00:59:33,304
I'm going to live well with Woo Joo.

884
00:59:33,304 --> 00:59:35,037
Let's eat.

885
00:59:36,486 --> 00:59:38,133
What is this place...

886
00:59:38,133 --> 00:59:40,083
How are you supposed to do this
all on your own?

887
00:59:40,083 --> 00:59:41,941
I'm going to pass, no matter what,

888
00:59:41,941 --> 00:59:44,377
and raise Woo Joo without him lacking anything.

889
00:59:45,816 --> 00:59:46,880
Please help!

890
00:59:46,880 --> 00:59:48,217
I'm going to give up Woo Joo.

891
00:59:48,217 --> 00:59:49,744
Daddy?

892
00:59:49,744 --> 00:59:50,768
Take him. Now.

893
00:59:50,768 --> 00:59:52,047
I'm done. We're cut off.

894
00:59:52,047 --> 00:59:53,588
You don't get to decide that on your own.

895
00:59:53,588 --> 00:59:55,084
We...

896
00:59:56,063 --> 00:59:58,303
We've already crossed that line.
